DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl");

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(2,5,1);
$x0 = random(2,5,1);
$y0 = $a1/$x0;
$x1 = $x0 + 0.1;
$x01 = $x0 + 0.01;
$x9 =  $x0 - 0.1;
$x99 = $x0- 0.01;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
The point \( P($x0 , $y0 ) \) lies on the curve
\( y = \frac{$a1}{x} \).  If \( Q \) is the point
\( (x, \frac{$a1}{x} ) \), find the slope of the secant line
\( PQ \) for the following values of \( x \).
$BR
If \( x= $x1 \), the slope of \( PQ \) is:
\{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans =-$a1/($x1*$x0);
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and if \( x= $x01 \), the slope of \( PQ \) is:
\{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans =-$a1/($x01*$x0);
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and if \( x= $x9 \), the slope of \( PQ \) is:
\{ans_rule(25)  \}
$BR
EOT

$ans =-$a1/($x9*$x0);
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and if \( x= $x99 \), the slope of \( PQ \) is:
\{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans =-$a1/($x99*$x0);
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Based on the above results, guess the slope of the tangent
line to the curve at \( P($x0 , $y0 ) \).
\{ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans =-$a1/($x0 ** 2 );
ANS(num_cmp($ans, relTol=>4));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
